<HEADLINE> UNICEF Lauds Indonesia's Children Protection Drive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 23 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations Children's
Funds (UNICEF) lauded Indonesia's national children protection
drive which President Soeharto launched here today during the
national children's day celebration.
</P>
<P>
Stephen J. Woodhouse, head of the UNICEF Representative Office
for Indonesia, said that the campaign is timely as
children-related problems emerging now are becoming complex and
multi-dimensional, and require inter-disciplinary measures and
involvement of various sectors.
</P>
<P>
He said UNICEF welcomes the Indonesian government's move to set
up a children's protection agency.
</P>
<P>
The government data also show that 60 percent of the 71,000
prostitutes being rehabilitated in government centers are aged
between 15 and 20 years.
</P>
<P>
Woodhouse said that although the condition is not as bad as
those in other countries, precautionary measures are needed to
address the problems as soon as possible. Meanwhile, Social
Affairs Minister Inten Soeweno said today that the government will
pay more attention to child protection through provision of
guarantees that protect abused, exploited and neglected children.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
