<HEADLINE> 7 Family Members Die in Traffic Accident in Egypt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, July 23 (Xinhua) -- Seven family members, including two
little girls, were killed and a number of others injured when a
microbus rammed into a parked truck in southern Egypt.
</P>
<P>
The 13 passengers who were riding in the microbus were all
family members, according to the Egyptian MENA news agency.
</P>
<P>
The collision happened on the desert road in Minya, about 230
kilometers south of Cairo.
</P>
<P>
The driver of the microbus also was killed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
