<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Net Foreign Assets of Nepali Banking Sector Up 1.4 Pc </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, July 23 (Xinhua) -- Net foreign assets of the
banking sector in Nepal increased by 1.4 percent to 38.235 billion
rupees (about 670 million U.S. dollars) during the first nine
months of the fiscal year 1996-97.
</P>
<P>
This percentage is 1.2 down compared with the same period of
the previous fiscal year, said the latest Economic Survey for
Fiscal Year 1996-97 ended July 14.
</P>
<P>
During this period, total internal credit rose only by 7.6
percent to 95.348 billion rupees (1.67 billion dollars), as
against an increase of 18.2 percent during the previous fiscal
year, the survey said.
</P>
<P>
The reason is that there has been a decline in the growth rate
of banking credit to the private sector, which accounts for a
two-thirds share in the total internal credit, the survey said.
</P>
<P>
Due to a decrease in industrial production and non-gold
imports, credit from commercial banks for industrial and
commercial purposes declined, leading to a sluggish growth of
banking credit to the private sector, the survey added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
