<HEADLINE> Urgent: Albanian President Resigns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, July 23 (Xinhua) -- Albanian President Sali Berisha
resigned this afternoon shortly before the first meeting of a new
parliament.
</P>
<P>
Berisha said that he resigned to show respect for his
Democratic Party which was defeated in elections on June 29, and
also show his determination not to form a coalition with the
Socialist Party. 
