<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jewish Settlers Assault Palestinian Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, July 23 (Xinhua) -- A senior Palestinian official
was attacked by Jewish settlers in the West Bank today, according
to a report of JMCC, a Palestinian press service based in East
Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
Abbas Zaki, member of the legislative Palestinian Council, was
attacked near Gilo Settlement while he was driving on his way to
the headquarters of the Palestinian council in Ramallah. The
settlers smashed the windshield of Zaki's car.
</P>
<P>
Zaki is also member of the central committee of Fatah, the
mainstream group of the Palestine Liberation Organization.
</P>
<P>
It was the second incident involving Fatah officials in two
days. Marwan Barghouteh, general secretary of Fatah and three
other senior Fatah activists were arrested by the Israeli
military authorities near Shilo in the West Bank Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
They are known to have ongoing contacts with the Israeli
left. Now they are reportedly detained at the Israeli army
headquarters in Beit El near Nablus. Israel has yet to comment on
the reason for their arrest.
</P>
<P>
The four Fatah officials had participated in a gathering
organized by Fatah in Nablus calling for the release of
Palestinian police officers. Hundreds of Fatah members gathered
outside a prison where Jihad Masini, a senior Palestinian police
officer, suspected of ordering attacks against Jewish settlers,
was being held.
</P>
<P>
Masini's arrest, which came reportedly under Israel's pressure,
particularly angered Fatah supporters. "The arrest of Fatah
fighters is a red line," said Taysir Nasralla, a Fatah
leader. 
</P>
</TEXT>
