<HEADLINE> India, Pakistan Should Sign Test Ban Treaty: Ikeda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 23 (Xinhua) -- Japanese Foreign Minister
Yukihiko Ikeda said here today that his country wants India and
Pakistan to sign Comprehensive Test Ban Treaty and Nuclear
Non-Proliferation Treaty.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Pakistan Television, Ikeda, who is on a
three-day visit to Pakistan, said that Japan would continue to
persuade leaders of India and Pakistan to sign the treaties aimed
at banning and preventing proliferation of nuclear weapons.
</P>
<P>
Ikeda said Pakistan was very important to Japan due to its
proximity to the Middle East and Central Asia. 
</P>
