<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fire Guts Paris Monument Museum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 23 (Xinhua) -- A mid-night fire gutted the interior
of the French Monument Museum and burnt down a great part of its
roof from Tuesday night to early this morning.
</P>
<P>
The damage was estimated at "million of francs," said museum
director Guy Cogeval.
</P>
<P>
Gas cylinders for welding placed at a repair work over-riding
the building were blamed for the cause of the fire, which
destroyed some plaster replicas of medieval Gothic art and damaged
some others.
</P>
<P>
The museum, situated at the Chaillot Palace across the Seine
river from the Eiffel Tower, displays French and European
monuments dating from Medieval Times to the 19th century, mainly
church reliefs, sculptures and statues.
</P>
<P>
The Museum of Cinema, which is sheltered in the same compound
and next to the monument galleries, was spared from the fire. But
all the films in it were evacuated to a nearby garden by
fire-fighters and its projection hall devastated by water.
</P>
<P>
Fire-fighters from 21 barracks were dispatched to the scene to
put down the fire, which burned for about four hours. 
</P>
</TEXT>
