<HEADLINE> Palestinian Maiden Flight Takes Off From Egypt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, July 23 (Xinhua) -- The first flight by the Palestinian
Airlines took off today from el-Arish in northeastern Egypt en
route to Amman.
</P>
<P>
Altogether 40 Palestinian passengers were ferried by vehicles
to Rafah, a Palestinian city bordering Egypt and then driven
another 40 kilometers to take the flight in the Arish airport, 320
kilometers northeast of Cairo, the Egyptian MENA news agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
Two other flights to Cairo and Athens, the Greek capital, will
also use Arish airport till pending issues with the Israeli side
as regards Gaza Airport are solved, said Head of the Palestinian
Civil Aviation Authority Brigadier Fayez Zeidan.
</P>
<P>
Construction of Gaza International Airport at Rafah came to
completion. But it has not been put into operation due to
disagreement between Israel and the Palestinian National Authority
on security arrangements at the site.
</P>
<P>
The official added that this issue tops the agenda of the
coming negotiations between the Palestinian and Israeli sides.
</P>
<P>
The Egyptian Civil Aviation Authority has agreed on opening
al-Arish airport for Palestinian planes until the inauguration of
the Gaza airport and allocated three offices and warehouses to
them, according to Director General of Arish Airport Mohamed Seif.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian flights with the rest of Arab and foreign countries
will soon be operated according to agreements signed betwee
..TIMEOUT

