<HEADLINE> Survey into Residential Building Collapse Incident is under Way </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, July 23 (Xinhua) -- Six people held responsible
directly for the collapse of a five-story building in a county of
east China's Zhejiang province is now in custody, and the county
procuratorial department has begun to look into their suspected
offences of dereliction of duty.
</P>
<P>
The five-storey residential building collapsed on the morning
of July 12 in Changshan County of Zhejiang province, leaving 36
people dead, and only three people survived.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, the incident aroused wide
repercussion in the Zhejiang province and the provincial
government has paid close attention to it. An investigation team
composed of 27 experts has been conducting a comprehensive survey
of the incident. 
</P>
</TEXT>
