<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rooming-House Fire Kills Four in Montreal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, July 23 (Xinhua) -- Four men were killed and one
injured in a fire at a rooming-house this morning in Canada's
second largest city of Montreal.
</P>
<P>
It is still not clear how the fire began in the three-story
building in the working class neighborhood of St-Henri of
Montreal, reports said.
</P>
<P>
At least one of the victims was burned to death in the fire,
which broke out on the second floor, police said.
</P>
<P>
One of the dead was found in a hallway, while the other two
died in their rooms.
</P>
<P>
The building has 14 rooms but only eight residents were in it
when the fire broke out. 
</P>
</TEXT>
