<HEADLINE> Albanian President Resigns After Party Defeat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, July 23 (Xinhua) -- Albanian President Sali Berisha
resigned this afternoon shortly before the first meeting of a new
parliament.
</P>
<P>
Berisha said on a television broadcast that he resigned to show
respect for his Democratic Party which was defeated in elections
on June 29, and also show his determination not to form a
coalition with the Socialist Party, reports said.
</P>
<P>
He said he would continue his politics in the parliament,
and support Albania's democratic and market values.
</P>
<P>
He said he would make efforts to help Albania integrate into
Europe and the European-Atlantic organs and properly resolve the
country's ethnic problem.
</P>
<P>
Berisha, elected president in 1992 for the first time, was the
second president after Ramiz Alia since Albania began multi-party
politics in 1990. He was reelected president in March,1997.
</P>
<P>
After the resignation, Berisha will keep his leading position
in the Democratic Party and act as the party's parliamentary
member. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
