<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, July 23 (Xinhua) -- Arab ambassadors in Bonn today
expressed "surprise and regret" at Germany's abstention from a
vote in the UN General Assembly last week which condemned Israel's
policy to build Jewish settlement in East Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
Describing it as a "negative message" to the Arab world, Arab
diplomats said Germany's abstention had raised the question about
the country's future policy towards the Middle East.
