<HEADLINE> Hussein Receives Invitation for OIC Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, July 23 (Xinhua) -- King Hussein of Jordan today
received an invitation from Iranian President Akbar Hashemi
Rafsanjani to attend the summit of the Organization of Islamic
Conference (OIC) due in Tehran in December.
</P>
<P>
The invitation was extended to the king by visiting Iranian
Minister of Industries Mohammed Reza Nematzadeh, Radio Jordan
reported.
</P>
<P>
It said that except for issues related to the Muslim world,
the invitation also dealt with Jordanian-Iranian ties and
bilateral cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian delegation led by Nematzadeh arrived here
Tuesday. They held talks on issues of economic cooperation with
their Jordanian counterparts Tuesday at the Jordanian Ministry of
Industry and Trade.
</P>
<P>
Nematzadeh told reporters after the talks that the joint
Jordanian-Iranian economic committee, which is due to hold its
meeting in Tehran later this year, will conclude agreements on
preventing dual taxation and on protection of investments in
both countries.
</P>
<P>
The volume of Jordanian exports to Iran rose from 4.3 million
Jordanian dinars (about 6 million U.S. dollars) in 1994 to 19.2
million dinars (about 27 million dollars) in 1995 and to 22.2
million dinars (about 31 million dollars) in 1996, semi-official
Jordan Times today quoted Nematzadeh as saying.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the kingdom`s imports from Iran increased from
5.1 million dinars (about 7.2 million dollars) in 1994 to 6
million dinars (about 8 million dollars) in 1995 and to 8.2
million dinars (about 11.6 million dollars) in 1996.
</P>
</TEXT>
