<HEADLINE> Ugandan President Leaves for Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, July 23 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan President Yoweri Museveni
left here today for Harare, Zimbabwe to attend the fourth Africa
African-American Summit.
</P>
<P>
Yoweri Museveni is accompanied in the visit by Ugandan First
Deputy Premier and Foreign Affairs Minister Eeriya Kategaya.
</P>
<P>
The on-going summit, attended by presidents from 20 African
countries and observers from Africa, the U.S., the Caribean and
other parts of the world, is seeking ways to attract trade
investment interest in Africa.
</P>
<P>
President Robert Mugabe of Zimbabwe is the summit host while
President Ketumile Masire of Botswana is the Chairman of the
Presidential Executive Committee of the summit.
</P>
<P>
The summit will include a number of separate workshops
organised along the themes as African art and culture, business
and economic development, communication and media, democracy,
education, health, population and women's issues. 
</P>
