<HEADLINE> Ugandan Ambassador on African-American Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, July 23 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan Ambassador to the United
States Edith Ssempala said here today the connection between
Africans and African-Americans has since the beginning of the
decade been getting deeper and broader, solidifying social,
political and economic links.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at an Africa African-American summit meeting,
Ssempala said this was happening at a critical moment for the
Afro-American relations when the continent was being viewed as a
partner rather than a recipient of aid.
</P>
<P>
The closer Afro-American relations had led to more initiatives
for investment in Africa by people from this and other
continents, she said.
</P>
<P>
Ssempala said she was pleased that the international community
was beginning to recognize and respond to the investment
potential in Africa.
</P>
<P>
To this end, she urged participants at the summit to cooperate
to help develop the continent.
</P>
<P>
The fourth bi-annual summit which began here Tuesday seeks ways
''to develop Africa and create business opportunities for
Africans and African-Americans''. 
</P>
</TEXT>
