<HEADLINE> Khamenei Urges Muslims to Tell Friends from Foes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 23 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Supreme Leader Ayatollah
Ali Khamenei today called on Muslims the world over to
distinguish friends from foes.
</P>
<P>
Khamenei issued the call while addressing a large audience of
visitors who are in Tehran on the occasion of the ongoing 10th
Islamic Unity Conference.
</P>
<P>
He said that "Shiites as well as Sunni Muslims must have a
realistic view of the current international situation and be
able to distinguish friends from foes."
</P>
<P>
The Iranian supreme leader stressed that "the world Muslims
must exploit their geographical and their other God-given
resources for their religious goals in their march to progress
and in their fight with international arrogance and Zionism."
</P>
<P>
He said that the unity of the Muslim world is the key to
solving the problems that are plaguing Muslim nations.
</P>
<P>
Historically, he said, the enemies of Muslims had always
feared the unity of world Muslims.
</P>
<P>
"The international enemies of Muslims have wrongly accused
Iran of supporting terrorism and human rights abuses with a view
to destroying the good relations between the Iranian government
and the rest of the Muslim world," he added.
</P>
<P>
Iran is to host the eighth summit of the Organization of the
Islamic Conference (OIC) in Tehran in December and has been
actively involved in overseas missions to invite leaders of the
Muslim countries to attend the summit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
