<HEADLINE> Dirty Water Kills 30,000 African Children Every </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, July 23 (Xinhua) -- At least 30,000 children under
five in Africa die every year due to problems related to
contaminated water, said a report presented to a health workshop at
the fourth African African-American summit here today.
</P>
<P>
A report of the water project for children in Africa initiated
at a summit in Gabon said many Africans did not have access to
safe water and the project was meant to resolve that problem.
</P>
<P>
''Water is life and the goal of the project is to provide safe
water to Africa,'' the report said.
</P>
<P>
Through the project, a group of African-Americans mobilized
funds to acquire equipment for safe water in Gabon, Kenya and
Benin.
</P>
<P>
The project is expected to train Africans to maintain their
water equipment and ensure sustainable water supply. 
</P>
