<HEADLINE> Arab Conference on Outer Space Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TUNIS, July 23 (Xinhua) -- Scientists, pilots and engineers
from 15 Arab states today discussed outer space technology and
related culture at an international conference held in Sussa, a
town 140 kilometers south of Tunis.
</P>
<P>
Experts and astronauts from the United States, Russia and
France also participated the Third Conference of the Arab
Organization of Aviation Culture (AOAC) which opened today.
</P>
<P>
The discussions focused on topics related to applied
experiences of outer space technology, dissimination of outer
space culture, the legal framework of outer space activities, life
in the outer space and the relationship between outer space
activities and economic and environmental development.
</P>
<P>
The AOAC will organize, on the sideline of the five-day
conference, a set of cultural activities, including a summer
academy where a group of 100 youths will receive applied and
theoretical lessons in outer space sciences, and an open aviation
festival that includes workshops for the launching of aircraft
and balloon models. 
</P>
