<HEADLINE> Ancient Tomb Discovered in Hebei </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, July 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese archaeologists have
discovered a tomb dating from the Western Jin Dynasty (265 to 316
A.D.) in the city of Baoding, north China's Hebei Province.
</P>
<P>
More than 40 historical relics, most of them pieces of pottery,
have been unearthed from the tomb.
</P>
<P>
Among them are black, white or red pottery items, trays, bowls,
pottery ox carts, copper coins, copper chips, bronze battle-axes,
knives and silver hairpins.
</P>
<P>
According to archaeologists, the discovery is of great
importance to the study of earthenware products and social life
during the Western Jin Dynasty.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
