<HEADLINE> France Reaffirms Support for Syrian Sovereignty Over Golan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 24 (Xinhua) -- France today reaffirmed its support
for Syria's claim of sovereignty over Golan Height, one day after
the Israeli parliament adopted a government bill aimed at banning
any withdrawal of Israeli troops from the height.
</P>
<P>
"Since the annexation in December 1981 of Golan Height, our
position remains that the negotiation between Israel and Syria
should resume as soon as possible on the basis of pertinent
resolutions of the U.N. Security Council, and the principle of
exchanging land for peace," said French foreign ministry spokesman
Jacques Rummelhardt.
</P>
<P>
He said that only a return of the sovereignty over Golan Height
to Syria can bring a solution to the security problems existing
between Israel and Syria.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli government bill requires the parliament to vote in
an ultra-absolute majority (80 votes out of a total of 120) to
pass any law in the future which can jeopardize the annexation of
Golan Height. 
</P>
</TEXT>
