<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Jiangsu Reports All-Round Economic Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, July 24 (Xinhua) -- East China's Jiangsu Province
experienced an all-round economic growth in the first half of
this year, official figures indicate.
</P>
<P>
The latest statistics show that the foreign trade volume of
Jiangsu, an economic powerhouse of China, jumped nearly 23.7
percent on a yearly basis in the first six months to more than
9.036 billion US dollars. Of the amount, exports reached 6.78
billion US dollars, up 26.18 percent.
</P>
<P>
Between January and June, foreign direct investment in Jiangsu
increased 25.6 percent to 2.56 billion US dollars. Investment from
Hong Kong and Macao, Japan, the United States, Singapore, and the
province of Taiwan exceeded 200 million US dollars each. The
Republic of Korea, Germany and the Netherlands invested more than
100 million US dollars each in Jiangsu in the first half of this
year.
</P>
<P>
As overall overseas investment in Jiangsu rose, average
investment in each project also went up in the first six months, a
provincial official noted.
</P>
<P>
Jiangsu's economic and technological cooperation with overseas
parties also expanded rapidly in the first half, as a total of 562
agreements for cooperation were signed during the period, with
contractual value totaling 477 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Also in the first half, Jiangsu approved another 12 state-owned
enterprises to set up production firms overseas.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970724.0068 </DOCNO>
