<DOCNO> XIE19970724.0070 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Anti-Taliban Forces Advance Near Kabul </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 24 (Xinhua) -- Forces opposing to the Afghan
Taliban militia are now only about 20 km north of the capital city
of Kabul after making major territorial gains today, sources said.
</P>
<P>
The forces led by former military chief Ahmad Masood have
advanced earlier in the day to the Mibachakot area, around 20 km
north of Kabul, said informed sources in Peshawar, a major city in
northwestern Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
Masood's forces are now posing to launch attack on the
Taliban-controlled area, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, several jets belonging to Uzbek warlord Abdul Malik,
another strongman in the anti-Taliban alliance, bombed the
downtown area of Kabul, killing at least 11 people including some
high Taliban officials, they said.
</P>
<P>
The bombs exploded near Arayana Hotel adjacent to the
presidential residence in Kabul. The hotel is used by the Taliban
government as a guest house.  
</P>
</TEXT>
