<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Soldier Killed in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, July 24 (Xinhua) -- A Nepalese serving in the Indian
army was killed Monday night by unknown assailants in Syangja
district of western Nepal, the official RSS news agency reported
today.
</P>
<P>
Mom Bahadur Gurung was returning home on leave when he was
stopped and killed by the assailants with a sharp weapon.
</P>
<P>
His body was then dumped into a gorge, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
When a passerby came up, the killers beat him before running
away, the RSS said.
</P>
<P>
The motive of killing is still unknown, and the police are
investigating, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
Under an agreement signed in August 1947 between Britain, India
and Nepal, the Nepalese are allowed to serve in the British and
Indian armies.  
</P>
</TEXT>
