<HEADLINE> Gonzalez out of Tour de France for Injury </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 24 (Xinhua) -- Colombian Chepe Gonzalez withdrew
from the Tour de France on Thursday because of a knee injury.
</P>
<P>
Gonzalez, a stage winner last year, pulled out about 20 km into
the 175.5 km 18th leg from Colmar at the start of the day's first
climb, said a report from Montbeliaro, France.
</P>
<P>
The Colombian cyclist was hurt in a fall on Wednesday and was
63rd overall.  
</P>
