<DOCNO> XIE19970724.0075 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UN Envoy Holds Talks with Afghan Taliban Leaders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 24 (Xinhua) -- United Nations Special Envoy on
Afghanistan Norbert Holl held talks today in Kandahar, a major
city in southern Afghanistan, with the leadership of the Islamic
Taliban militia.
</P>
<P>
Holl's two-hour talks with Taliban's Governor of Kandahar
Muhammad Hassan Rahmani and its acting Foreign Minister Mullah
Abdul Jalil focused on the prospect of a ceasefire between the
Taliban and their rival northern alliance led by former military
chief Ahmad Masood and Uzbek warlord Abdul Malik, Pakistan
Television (PTV) reported.
</P>
<P>
The UN envoy would then visit Mazar-e-Sharif, headquarters of
the northern alliance and about 300 km north of Kabul, next week
to brief leaders of the alliance on the outcome of his talks with
the Taliban, it said.
</P>
<P>
Over the past few days, forces loyal to Masood have made
significant territorial gains by capturing the strategic Bagram
airbase, about 50 km north of Kabul, and they are now closing in
on the beleaguered Afghan capital.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
