<BODY>
<HEADLINE> South China City Successful In Combating Drug Crimes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, July 24 (Xinhua) -- South China's city of Haikou, the
capital of Hainan Province, has solved 61 drug trafficking cases
and seized more than 1.5 kg of heroin as part of an anti-drug
campaign launched since this May.
</P>
<P>
Local police have broken up three gangs involved in drug
trafficking, apprehended 60 suspects and confiscated more than
300,000 yuan (36,000 US dollars) worth of illegal substances
over the past two months.
</P>
<P>
Drug crimes have increased in the city over recent years. Last
year, 35 percent of the criminal cases were drug-related.
</P>
<P>
The city has stepped up its efforts to fight drug crimes, and
as a result,the number of criminal cases has decreased in the
first half of the year, compared with last year's January-June
period. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
