<DOCNO> XIE19970724.0080 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Anhui Sees Half-Year Foreign Trade up Slightly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, July 24 (Xinhua) -- The foreign trade volume of east
China's Anhui Province was up 4.4 percent to 1.05 billion US
dollars in the first half of this year, the latest statistics show.
</P>
<P>
Breakdowns show that exports surged 24 percent to 680 million
US dollars between January and June, while imports slumped from a
year ago to 370 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
A further analysis indicates that general exports rose 21
percent in the first six months to 490 million US dollars, with
machinery, electronics, household electric appliances, and farm
produce being the leading export items.
</P>
<P>
The half-year trade surplus of 310 million US dollars was over
200 million US dollars more than in the same 1996 period.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970724.0081 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Outline Agreement Reached on New CFE Treaty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, July 24 (Xinhua) -- The 30 nations revising the
Conventional Forces in Europe (CFE) here on Wednesday reached a
framework agreement to further reduce the conventional arms
stationed in Europe, said a report of the Austria Presse Agentur
(APA).
</P>
<P>
The 16 NATO members and the 14 countries which used to form the
rival Warsaw Pact agreed that there would be significantly less
equipment permitted in the area of application in Europe than
there was under the original treaty.
</P>
<P>
The original treaty allowed one overall amount of equipment for
NATO members and an equal amount for the Warsaw Pact, with a
system setting national ceilings.
</P>
<P>
The new treaty would fix ceilings on the amount of equipment
that a given country could station anywhere within the CFE area,
which goes from the Atlantic to the Urals.
</P>
<P>
It would also set ceilings on the amount of equipment that
could be stationed by a country, or its allies, within any given
country, or in certain cases, parts of a country.
</P>
<P>
Washington hailed the outline agreement as ushering in an era
of "cooperation not confrontation," the APA report quoted sources
from the White House as saying.
</P>
<P>
Robert Bell of the U.S. National Security Council said
"cooperation not confrontation" marked the Vienna talks, which
began in February. He added that a final agreement was expected to
be concluded within a year.
</P>
<P>
The CFE negotiations represented a key tool in persuading
Russia to accept NATO's expansion to include former Warsaw Pact
members -- the Czech Republic, Hungary and Poland.
</P>
<P>
Russia sees it as a means to make sure NATO will not build up
its forces along its eastern flank. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970724.0082 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Somali Clan Clashes Kill at Least Three </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, July 24 (Xinhua) -- At least three people were
killed and two others wounded in Somalia when fighting erupted
Tuesday evening between militiamen from the Hawadle Clan and
others belonging to the Rer Aw-Hassan clan at Abalei Village, 45
km north of the central town of Beletuein.
</P>
<P>
According to reports from the region, about 30 heavily armed
Hawadle clansmen in two battle wagons attacked on Abalei
villagers in the evening, and were faced with serious resistance
from the militiamen of the village who had most probably been
aware of the attack to come.
</P>
<P>
Travelers to the capital Mogadishu from the area said today
that eight people including militiamen were also missing as many
people jumped into the river in an attempt to escape the
fighting.
</P>
<P>
A lorry driver who passed by the village immediately after the
fighting said he saw two donkeys bleeding from bullet wounds just
outside the village which looked like a deserted place.
</P>
<P>
There's no official word from either side over the cause for
the fighting. However, reports said the two sides have long been
arguing about the ownership of a farmland at the river bank near
the village.
</P>
<P>
The less-armed community of Rer Aw-Hassan claimed that the
land is theirs and that the Hawadle attackers wanted to take
their farms at gunpoint, according to the report.
</P>
<P>
This is the second time the Hawadle men attack their village,
said the Rer Aw-Hassan clan.
</P>
<P>
Elders from the two sides have left Beletuein district, 300 km
north of Mogadishu, to see what had happened in Abalei village.
</P>
<P>
The elders include traditional leaders and religious men who
want to exert effort in ending the dispute between the two sides
with the help of the Islamic sharia judgement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
