fix results of English Premiership matches with three other men,
reports said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Coach Ian Porterfield wants the former Liverpool star to play
in Angola on Sunday because first-chioce Gift Muzadzi is suffering
a knee injury and reserve Ernest Chirambadare is off-form.
</P>
<P>
The 39-year-old Grobbelaar missed recent World and African Cup
qualifiers in Togo and Ghana due to court appearances.
</P>
<P>
Zimbabwe has reached the finals in the Nations Cup for the
first time after eight disappointed attempts.  
