<DOCNO> XIE19970724.0087 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Qingdao Beer Festival Dries Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINGDAO, July 24 (Xinhua) -- This port city in eastern China's
Shandong Province wound up its 16-day international beer
festival 1997 Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
More than 40 Chinese and foreign breweries, with 77 well-known
brands of beer, attended the largest-ever beer festival in China.
</P>
<P>
A record 40 tons of beer or more was sold every day during
the festival.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the International Beer and Beverage Fair, held in
tandem with the beer festival, drew over 200 beverage
manufacturers from throughout the world.
</P>
<P>
A total of 1.12 million Chinese and overseas visitors arrived
at the Shilaoren National Tourism Resort in suburban Qingdao for
the festivities.
</P>
<P>
The sponsors of the events were the Qingdao City Government,
National Tourism Administration, Ministry of Internal Trade, China
Council for the Promotion of International Trade, China Chamber of
International Commerce and Chinese People's Association for
Friendship with Foreign Countries. 
</P>
