<HEADLINE> Syrian Media Slam Israeli Knesset Resolution </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, July 24 (Xinhua) -- Syrian media today described
Israel's Knesset (parliament) resolution on Golan Heights as an
act to undermine the efforts to salvage the deadlocked
Syrian-Israeli peace talks.
</P>
<P>
Israel's Knesset approved Wednesday a bill forbidding an
Israeli withdrawal from Syrian Golan Heights occupied by Israel in
1967. In a vote to the bill, 43 Knesset members voted for, 40
others voted against, while 3 abstained.
</P>
<P>
Syrian media described the bill as an attempt to challenge the
relevant UN resolutions and to ignore the Middle East peace
process principles agreed upon at the Madrid conference.
</P>
<P>
Syrian Media added that resolution defies the world public
opinion calling for an Israeli withdrawal from all the occupied
Arab territories, including Jerusalem and the Golan Heights.
</P>
<P>
Syrian newspaper "Al-Baath", the mouthpiece of the ruling party,
in its editorial today said that the aforesaid bill has exposed
Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu completely to the whole
world and proved the falsity of his presumptions about peace.
</P>
<P>
The state-controlled Syrian newspaper "Al-Thawara" said in a
commentary today that the resolution is an Israeli provocative
move that assures the whole world that Israel does not want peace.
</P>
<P>
Israel's Knesset passed a bill in 1981 on annexing the Syrian
Golan Heights. 
</P>
</TEXT>
