<DOCNO> XIE19970724.0102 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Albanian New President, PM, Parliament Speaker Elected </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, July 24 (Xinhua) -- Albania elected its new president,
prime minister and parliament speaker today at a meeting of the
new parliament, the 15th parliament of Albania.
</P>
<P>
Socialist Party Secretary General Rexhep Mejdani was elected the
president, and Socialist Party Chairman Fatos Nano and Socialist
Democratic Party Chairman Skender Gjinushi were elected as prime
minister and parliament speaker respectively.
</P>
<P>
Mejdani, a 53-year-old professor and a physicist, was elected
to replace Sali Berisha, who resigned Wednesday to avoid forming a
coalition with the Socialist Party.
</P>
<P>
Mejdani was a member of the presidium of parliament in 1991. In
September 1996, he was elected secretary general of the Socialist
Party and became a parliament member in June 1997.
</P>
<P>
Nano, 45, an economist and politician, acted as vice prime
minister in charge of economic reforms in the country in
January-February 1991.
</P>
<P>
He was prime minister of the caretaker government between March
and May in 1991, responsible for preparing for Albania's first
multi-party elections on March 31 that year.
</P>
<P>
During the 1991 election, Nano was elected prime minister in
the multi-party parliament.
</P>
<P>
He became Socialist Party chairman in 1992 and 1996. In July
1993, he was arrested on charges of economic crimes by the
Democratic Party authorities.
</P>
<P>
Nano had been a key political opponent of Berisha till March 14,
1997 when he was released from prison under a presidential decree.
</P>
<P>
Gjinushi, 38, was elected education minister in 1981. In
February 1991, he resigned over open disputes with the Labor Party
authorities over his support for university students movement in
December 1990.
</P>
<P>
Afterwards, he established a central-leftist opposition party
-- the Socialist Democratic Party -- along with some intellectuals.
</P>
<P>
Gjinushi has been chairman of his party since then. He was
elected parliament member in March 1992. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
