<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-Premier Meets Japanese Former Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier and Foreign
Minister Qian Qichen today told former Japanese Prime Minister
Morihiro Hosokawa that China appreciates Hosokawa's efforts to
develop Sino-Japanese ties, as well as his stand on accurately
viewing historical facts, learning from the past, and facing the
future with a sense of deep introspection.
</P>
<P>
