relations, the Taiwan issue, the situation in Cambodia and the
Korean peninsula issue.
</P>
<P>
Hosokawa said that Japanese Prime Minister Ryutaro Hashimoto
will visit China in this September, while in November, Chinese
Premier Li Peng will tour Japan.
</P>
<P>
Hosokawa also said that he is convicted that bilateral
relations will make still greater progress under the new
situation, and contribute greatly to the peace and development of
Asia and the world as a whole.
</P>
<P>
Hosokawa and his party arrived here yesterday as guests of the
Chinese People's Institute of Foreign Affairs. 
