<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Oil-Bearing Strata Discovered in Northern Qaidam Basin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, July 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese petroleum geological
workers have discovered 72 new oil-bearing strata in a recent oil
drilling in northern Qaidam Basin, northwest China's Qinghai
Province.
</P>
<P>
According to Ma Lining, chief geologist of Prospecting and
Development Institute of Qinghai Petroleum Administration, the oil
drilling was done at the Xianliu Well in Qaidam Basin's Nanbaxian
Area.
</P>
<P>
It is expected that 30 million tons of oil and gas (1,000 cu m
of gas equals to one ton of oil) reserves will be verified in this
well this year, said Ma. Geological workers have also discovered
an industrial oil gusher with a daily gas output exceeding 100,000
cu m at two other oil wells in the same region of Nanbaxian.
</P>
<P>
Ma predicted there are high hopes for Nanbaxian Region to
become another medium-sized oilfield with big exploration value,
second only to the Ghasi Kola Oilfield, which has more than 100
million tons of geological oil-gas reserves. It was discovered 20
years ago in Qaidam Basin.
</P>
<P>
Nanbaxian Region is one of the eight key oil and gas
prospecting and development areas designated by China National Oil
Corporation as sites where significant breakthroughs should be
made this year. The list also includes Sebei Region of Qaidam
Basin.
</P>
<P>
Qaidam Basin, with an area of 240,000 sq km, is one of China's
four major basins. It now produces 4,300 tons of oil-gas daily.
</P>
<P>
Qinghai Petroleum Administration has discovered in the
northwestern part of Qadam Basin a deposit environment similar to
that of Ghasi Kola Oilfield, and has intensified gas prospecting
work in the basin's central area.
</P>
<P>
It is expected 40 billion cu m of newly-discovered geological
gas reserves will be proven this year.
</P>
<P>
The administration also plans to increase the amount of
verified oil and gas reserves from the present 200 million tons to
600 million tons, and raise its annual gas output from the current
1.5 million tons to three million tons by the turn of this
century. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
