<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Largest Digital Microwave Making Line Operational in Xi'an </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 24 (Xinhua) -- The most technically sophisticated
production line for synchronous digital hierarchy (SDH) microwave
equipment, one the world's fastest digital telecom transmission
systems, has been in operation in Xi'an, capital of Shaanxi
Province, since July 8.
</P>
<P>
According the latest issue of the People's Post and
Telecommunications News, the production line, launched in Xi'an's
Fujitsu Telecom Equipment Ltd., will be the first maker of SDH
microwave equipment in China, and ease the country's dependence on
foreign SDH products.
</P>
<P>
The production line will specialize in making the SDH microwave
equipment with a frequency form four GHz to 23 GHz. The
transmission speed of the SDH products will reach 155 Mb per
second or 2*155 Mb per second.
</P>
<P>
Involving an initial investment of 9.8 million US dollars,
Xi'an Fujitsu is a joint venture funded by Fujitsu, the leading
Japanese telecom supplier, and a local telecom firm in January
1996. In addition to the SDH microwave equipment, the venture has
extended its product range to the wireless local loop system, CDMA
(Code Diversion Multiple Accesses) equipment and a satellite
telecom system. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970724.0109 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Killer of Italian Fashion Designer Found Dead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 24 (Xinhua) -- Andrew Cunanan, the suspected
killer of Italian fashion designer Gianni Versace, was found dead
in a houseboat at Miami Beach, Florida on Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
More than 100 police and Federal Bureau of Investigation (FBI)
agents surrounded the two-story house Wednesday night after a
report of a gunshot coming from inside. Cunanan's body was found
several hours after police and FBI officers moved into the house
when they got no response to their shout.
</P>
<P>
Cunanan was identified by his thumbprint and the gun found
inside the houseboat was similar to the one used in three of five
killings in which Cunanan was a suspect.
</P>
<P>
The 27-year-old Cunanan was on the top of the FBI's most wanted
list as the prime suspect in the slayings of Versace on July 15
and four other men in Minnesota, Illinois and New Jersey.
</P>
<P>
A .40-caliber handgun, the same type of weapon Cunanan was
believed to have used in his cross-country killing spree, was
found near the body, television reports said.
</P>
<P>
After the slaying of the fashion designer, an intensive
nationwide search for Cunanan was launched. Cunanan managed to
escape capture even though his picture was plastered on
television, newspapers, the Internet and wanted posters. 
</P>
</TEXT>
