<HEADLINE> China's Largest Digital Microwave Making Line Operational in Xi'an </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 24 (Xinhua/OANA) -- The most technically
sophisticated production line for synchronous digital hierarchy
(SDH) microwave equipment, one the world's fastest digital telecom
transmission systems, has been operational in Xi'an, capital of
Shaanxi Province, since July 8.
</P>
<P>
According the latest issue of the People's Post and
Telecommunications News, the production line, launched in Xi'an's
Fujitsu Telecom Equipment Ltd., will be the first maker of SDH
microwave equipment in China, and ease the country's dependence on
foreign SDH products.
</P>
<P>
The production line will specialize in making the SDH microwave
equipment with a frequency form four GHz to 23 GHz. The
transmission speed of the SDH products will reach 155 Mb per
second or 2*155 Mb per second.
</P>
<P>
Involving an initial investment of 9.8 million US dollars,
Xi'an Fujitsu is a joint venture funded by Fujitsu, the leading
Japanese telecom supplier, and a local telecom firm in January
