<HEADLINE> 32 Tamil Rebels Killed in North Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 24 (Xinhua) -- At least 32 Tamil rebels were
killed Wednesday by government troops in Northern province of Sri
Lanka, according to a military spokesman here today.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said at today's press briefing that the incident
took place about four kilometers west of Nedunkerni, killing 32
rebels and injuring 25 others.
</P>
<P>
He added that four government soldiers were also killed and 11
others injured in the encounter.
</P>
<P>
He said that Sri Lanka's air force provided air cover and the
troops repulsed the rebels, forcing them to flee.
</P>
<P>
Tiger radio confirmed the incident and said that 32 of its
cadres were killed in battle, the spokesman added.
</P>
<P>
The government troops have been engaged in Operation Jaya
Sikuru (certain victory), which was launched on May 14 to open a
key supply line along a highway linking South to the Jaffna
Peninsula.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been fighting a war for a separate state
in the north and east of the country since 1983.  
