<HEADLINE> Tung Urges Hong Kong Citizens to Be Patient on Housing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 24 (Xinhua) -- The Chief Executive of the Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR), Tung Chee-hwa, has
urged Hong Kong residents to be patient while his government moves
 to stabilize property prices, according to a press release
circulated here today.
</P>
<P>
During his first district visit on Hong Kong Island on
Wednesday since the July 1 handover, Tung stressed that tackling
housing and land worries remained a priority for his government.
</P>
