But he hinted that no administrative measures would be taken, a
move appeared to be aimed at reassuring developers.
</P>
<P>
He said suppressing rocketing flat prices was a long-term
process that could not be resolved in the near future. The
government would strive to strike a balance between supply and
demand by providing more land for its enhanced housing program, he
added.
</P>
<P>
