<HEADLINE> SIMEX Extends Nikkei Futures Trading Hours </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, July 24 (Xinhua) -- The Singapore International
Monetary Exchange (SIMEX) announced today that it will be
extending the trading hours of its Nikkei 225 and Nikkei 300
futures contracts to 7:00 p.m. Singapore time, starting from
September 3 this year.
</P>
<P>
It said that trading during the extended hours will be done
electronically on SIMEX automated trading system (ATS).
</P>
<P>
"An agreement was signed on July 22, 1997 between SIMEX and the
Nihon Keizai Shimbun, the proprietor of the Nikkei stock indices,
for the ATS trading to begin on September 3, 1997 which is a
significant day itself, being the 11th birthday of Nikkei 225
futures," the SIMEX said.
</P>
<P>
It also said that the extension of trading hours represents yet
another move by the SIMEX to strengthen its position as the center
of equity index futures trading in Asia.
</P>
<P>
"The Exchange (the Stock Exchange of Singapore) is always
willing to enhance its facility for futures trading so long as the
customers see the need. We are confident that the trading facility
provided through our ATS will enable our customers to trade or
hedge even more effectively on SIMEX," said Victor Liew, chairman
of the SIMEX.  
</P>
</TEXT>
