<HEADLINE> Laos, Myanmar Pledge to Contribute to Regional Peace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PETALING JAYA, MALAYSIA, July 24 (Xinhua) -- Laos and Myanmar,
both new members of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations
(ASEAN), today pledged to cooperate with all other member
countries in building up and safeguarding peace in the region and
the world as a whole.
</P>
<P>
Laos and Myanmar were officially admitted into the ASEAN fold
yesterday, bringing the number of ASEAN members from seven to
nine.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the opening session of the 30th ASEAN Ministerial
Meeting here today, Lao Foreign Minister Somsavat Lengsavad said
that as an ASEAN member, his country will continue to pursue its
foreign policy of peace, independence, friendship and cooperation
and fulfill its commitments by cooperating in all fields with
other members, thus contributing to enhancing the strength, unity
and prosperity of ASEAN.
</P>
<P>
"Laos will relentlessly further expand its cooperation with
foreign countries and contribute, at its capability, to the common
cause of enhancing peace, stability and promoting cooperation for
the development in the region and in the world," he said.
</P>
<P>
Laos will also continue to cooperate with all member countries
in maintaining peace and finding peaceful solutions to various
problems in the region and the world at large, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Lao minister said that by strengthening solidarity,
cooperation and mutual assistance among ASEAN member countries,
Southeast Asia will become a region of prosperity and its people
will enjoy peaceful life.
</P>
<P>
In his speech, Myanmar Foreign Minister U Ohn Gyaw said that
regional stability is the combined result of individual
achievements of national stability by the countries in the region.
"Only with harmonious development of the political, economic and
social spheres in each country can we aspire for a harmonious
achievement of regional progress and security."
</P>
<P>
In maintaining peace and stability in the region, ASEAN's track
record stands as a "shining example" for all, he said.
</P>
<P>
"We in Myanmar are aware now more than ever of the importance
of shared objectives and combined efforts for a situation where
all can enjoy the happy end result," the minister said.
</P>
<P>
He said Myanmar will do its best to maintain the harmony of
development at both the national and regional levels.
</P>
<P>
A peaceful, prosperous, modern and developed Myanmar with
harmony in political development, social cohesiveness and economic
growth is important for ASEAN's shared objective of regional peace
and prosperity, he said.
</P>
<P>
He pledged that as a responsible member of ASEAN, Myanmar looks
forward to increased participation in and enhanced contribution to
the process of achieving peace, stability and the well-being of
the region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
