<HEADLINE> Tour Groups to Macao Increase in 1st 5 Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, July 24 (Xinhua) -- The number of visitors coming to
Macao in tour groups in the first five months of the year grew
15.7 percent from the same period of last year, latest statistics
show.
</P>
<P>
The number of group travelers reached 530,360 by the end of May
this year, with the dominant part of them from China's interior,
Taiwan and Japan, according to figures released by the Macao
Census and Statistics Department today.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a total of 1,030,158 passengers checked in Macao
hotels during the period, down 1.7 percent. The average rate of
room occupancy in Macao hotels arrived at 59.1 percent, down 0.5
percent from the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The total number of travelers to Macao dropped by 2.4 percent
in the first five months to 3,200,913, earlier figures show.
</P>
<P>
Macao tourism officials had expected the number of tourists to
reach nine million this year, after it surpassed 8.15 million last
year.
</P>
<P>
Tourism is a major income earner for Macao with a population of
450,000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
