<HEADLINE> Rafsanjani Orders Tank, APC Mass Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 24 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Hashemi
Rafsanjani today commissioned the mass production of tanks and
armored personnel carriers by two important plants near the
capital.
</P>
<P>
Iran's official news agency IRNA reported that the president
inaugurated the mass production in the two plants located at
Shahid Kolahdouz Industrial Complex in Karaj, about 50 northwest
of Tehran.
</P>
<P>
IRNA said that in the presence of Rafsanjani, the production of
Zolfaqar tank, which has a speed of 65 kilometers per hour, went
on stream.
</P>
<P>
It said the armored personnel carrier (APC), Borra, is the
first such designed and manufactured by Iranian defense industries
to meet the needs of armed forces.
</P>
<P>
In the initial stage, 40 carriers have been produced and
delivered to the Islamic Revolution's Guards Corps (IRGC). Each
carrier has a capacity of 12 crew and is equipped with a 50-mm
gun. It can be utilized in various military missions and has a
speed of 65 kilometers an hour, it said.
</P>
<P>
Another type of APC, BMT-2, with a 30-mm gun, a capacity of
seven crew and a speed of 65 kilometers per hour, also went into
mass production today, it added.
</P>
<P>
There is no mention of the basic specifications of the tanks
and APCs. Military specialists here said that some parts of the
tank are imported from Russia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
