<HEADLINE> Carl Lewis to Run in Berlin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, July 23 (Xinhua) -- Carl Lewis will run his last
competitive race August 26 in Berlin, report said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Lewis, winner of nine Olympic gold medals and a record eight
world championship golds, will join a 400-meter relay team
including his Santa Monica Track Club teammates Leroy Burrell,
Mike Marsh and Floyd Heard to run his last competitive race in an
International Amateur Athletic Federation Grand Prix meet.
</P>
<P>
"That will definitely be his last competitive race," his coach
Tom Tellez in Houston was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Lewis, 36, will end his illustrious career September 13 in an
exhibition relay on his home track at Robertson Stadium in Houston
during pregame or halftime festivities of the Pittsburgh-Houston
game.  
</P>
