<DOCNO> XIE19970724.0135 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cambodia Not to Accept ASEAN's Interference, Says Hun sen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, July 24 (Xinhua) -- Cambodian Second Prime Minister
Hun Sen said today that his country acknowledged the role played
by the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) in achieving
peace and stability in Cambodia but will not accept ASEAN's
interference in its internal affairs.
</P>
<P>
"We accept ASEAN's role in realizing peace and stability in
Cambodia, but we do not accept its interference in our internal
affairs," Hun Sen told a news conference after a cabinet meeting.
</P>
<P>
The Cambodian National Assembly and the royal government will
continue to handle internal affairs by respecting the constitution
and the King, Hun Sen added.
</P>
<P>
Last Saturday, Hun Sen rejected ASEAN's mediation for a
solution to Cambodia's political crisis.
</P>
<P>
When asked about ASEAN's refusal to admit Cambodia as
scheduled, Hun Sen said, "We respect its decision. But our common
strategic goal is that ASEAN should have 10 members not nine."
</P>
<P>
Laos and Maynmar were admitted into ASEAN Wednesday at the
organization's ministerial meeting in Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
The meeting reiterated ASEAN's decision on July 10 to defer the
admission of Cambodia because of the conflicts between the
country's prime ministers in Phnom Penh in early July. 
</P>
</TEXT>
