<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Sharemarket Closes All-time High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 24 (Xinhua) -- The 33-member blue-chip index
added 292.03 points to end at 15,738.81 on Wednesday, surpassing
the previous record of 15,706.29 set last Thursday.
</P>
<P>
This 1.89-percent rise, due to the influence from Wall Street's
 new record 154-point close and the soaring worth of Hong Kong's
financial and property shares, became the fifth record of its kind
 since Hong Kong's July 1 return to the motherland, experts here
believe.
</P>
<P>
Wall Street shares' high close came in reaction to comments by
U.S. Federal Reserve chairman Alan Greenspan on Tuesday night,
which were seen by investors as suggesting federal policy remained
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Greenspan's testimony before the United States Congress praised
the overall state of the economy and implied that as growth had
slowed and inflation was still low, no changes in monetary policy
were envisaged in the near future.
</P>
<P>
He said that his department had raised its forecast for
economic growth to between 3 and 3.25 percent for this year, up
from last year's 2.4 percent, and consumer price inflation was
seen at 2.25 to 2.5 percent this year, lower than last year's
figure.
</P>
<P>
U.S. bond yields retreated on the testimony, which came early
Wednesday morning, sending Wall Street to a new record close. It
ended 154 points higher at 8,061 and set the stage for Wednesday's
gains in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong trading opened strongly and quickly, with the Hang
Seng Index advancing to an intra-day high of 15,738.81 points. All
four sectors of the Hang Seng Index closed higher, with
rate-sensitive financials and properties leading the gains, after
three days of losses.
</P>
<P>
The biggest gainer was financial group HSBC. Sun Hung Kai
Properties Ltd, the largest property company in terms of market
capitalization, was the second-biggest index gainer. Hutchison
Whampoa Ltd and Hong Kong Telecommunications Ltd also boosted the
index. 
</P>
</TEXT>
