<HEADLINE> HK Residents Invited to Give Views on Constituency Delineation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 24 (Xinhua) -- The government of the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) has urged the public to give
their views on the delineation of the electorate for the nine new
functional constituencies and the seven designated groups of the
Election Committee.
</P>
<P>
The deadline for submission is July 31, said a press release
reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
"The proposed lists of electorate for the nine new functional
constituencies and the seven designated groups of the Election
Committee are now published for public consultation," it quoted a
HKSAR government spokesman as saying.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the government's objective is that the first
legislative election should be "open, fair and honest." The new
legislative body is expected to be elected next summer.
</P>
<P>
According to an earlier decision of the HKSAR government, nine
new functional constituencies -- covering sports, performing arts,
culture and publication, labor (one additional seat), import and
export, textiles and garment, wholesale and retail, information
technology, transport, agriculture and fisheries, and insurance --
will be introduced for the first HKSAR Legislative Council
Election.
</P>
<P>
As for the Election Committee, it will be made up of 800
members from four different sectors, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Apart from the relevant functional constituencies and
designated organizations, members of the committee will also
compromise representatives from seven other groups such as the
Hong Kong Chinese Enterprise Association, hotel, Chinese medicine,
higher education, catering, the Employers' Federation of Hong Kong
and religion.
</P>
<P>
"In delineating the electorate concerned, we have followed the
traditional concept and criteria for the delineation of functional
constituency electorate," the spokesman said, noting that "there
are also the concept and criteria used in delineating the
electorate for the 21 old functional constituencies."
</P>
<P>
In his words, the functional constituencies will be composed of
major organizations representative of the relevant sectors, and
particular groups or bodies should not be represented in more than
one functional constituency.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
