<HEADLINE> Chinese CMC Vice-Chairman Meets Former U.S. President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 24 (Xinhua) -- China said today that it values
the Sino-U.S. relations very much and hopes that the two countries
would develop a long-term and stable friendship and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Chi Haotian, vice-chairman of the Central Military Commission
(CMC), made the remarks at a meeting with the visiting former
U.S. President Jimmy Cater in the Great Hall of the People here
today.
</P>
<P>
Chi, also a Chinese State Councillor and defence minister,
described Cater as an old friend of China. He said that the
Chinese people would not forget that it was during Cater's term as
US President that China and the US normalized their relations and
established their diplomatic ties, Chi said.
</P>
<P>
They would not forget either that it was Carter, the then US
president, who invited Deng Xiaoping to visit the United States,
he noted, adding that the people of the world still remember
Deng's contributions to the develoment of the Sino-U.S. relations
though he has passed away.
</P>
<P>
Chi stressed: "China values the Sino-US relations very much and
hopes for a long-term and stable Sino-US friendship and
cooperation."
</P>
<P>
He appreciated Carter's effort to work for world peace and
stability even after he left his post as the US president. He said
that China and the U.S., both as big countries, should make
greater contributions to world peace and stability.
</P>
<P>
Carter thanked Chi's friendly remarks, saying the remarks
showed that the Chinese military leaders fully understand the
importance of a continuous development of the relations between
the US and China.
</P>
<P>
Both also exchanged views on other issues of common concern.
</P>
<P>
Carter and his party arrived here Wednesday as guests of the
Chinese People's Institute of Foreign Affairs.  
</P>
