<HEADLINE> Beijing Banks to Offer Mortgage Loans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 24 (Xinhua) -- Beijing's two commercial banks
will begin offering individual mortgage loans on July 28.
</P>
<P>
Today's Beijing Youth Daily reported that Beijing branches of
the China Industrial and Commercial Bank and the China
Construction Bank will become the first financial institutions in
the Chinese capital to offer mortgage loan services.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing Housing Funds Management Center adopted mortgage
regulations governing individual home loans on July 1.
</P>
<P>
The center's director said that numerous people have sought
specific advice, with most inquiring about mortgage application
requirements.
</P>
<P>
The funds management center and its affiliates will provide the
bulk of funding for the program.
</P>
<P>
Permanent Beijing residents contributing to company or
government housing accumulation funds can apply for mortgage
loans from the aforementioned banks.
</P>
<P>
Loans will carry a 25-year term, with loan ceilings set at
300,000 yuan (36,100 US Dollars) or 70 percent of the total cost
of the property. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
