<HEADLINE> Iran to Manufacture Six Destroyers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 24 (Xinhua) -- The Iranian navy will start
manufacturing six multi-purpose destroyers in the near future,
Rear Admiral Abbas Mohtaj, a deputy commander, said here today.
</P>
<P>
According to the official news agency IRNA, the deputy commander
said planning and designing of the huge project have been
completed and production will start after the approval of the
command headquarters of the Iranian armed forces.
</P>
<P>
He was quoted as saying that building of the six destroyers
will be part of a nationwide effort to confront the potential
military threat by the United States and Israel.
</P>
<P>
There were no details about those destroyers. Earlier reports
said the Iranian navy at present has three destroyers, five
frigates, three submarines and 10 fast patrol missile crafts.
</P>
<P>
The high-ranking officer also called for more contacts between
the navy and research and scientific centers in order to improve
its military capability and combativeness.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian armed forces have been building up its military
prowess through establishment of missile and radar bases,
purchase of submarines and missile boats which have been deployed
off its northern coast in the Persian Gulf.
</P>
<P>
To better confront potential attacks by the U.S., Iran raised
its budget for the military by over 40 percent in the new fiscal
year starting March 21, 1991.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, the government has allocated 25 billion
rials (8.3 million U.S. dollars) on work to counter U.S.
conspiracies against the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
