<DOCNO> XIE19970724.0151 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ASEAN Urged to Sustain Dynamism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PETALING JAYA, Malaysia, July 24 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian Foreign
Minister Abdullah Ahmad Badawi today urged all members of the
Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) to sustain the
grouping's dynamism in the 21st century through continued
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
"As the ASEAN stands at the threshold of the 21st century, it
faces the daunting task of sustaining its dynamism and maintaining
its track record," Badawi, who is the current chairman of the
ASEAN Standing Committee, told the opening of the 30th ASEAN
Ministerial Meeting (AMM).
</P>
<P>
"We have done well so far, but success and prosperity often
breed complacency," he said. "Our task is made more difficult by
the more complex environment of the next millennium characterized
by the blossoming of the information age, globalization and
intensified regionalism."
</P>
<P>
However, Badawi declared that "With our 30 years of experience
and continued commitment to ASEAN cooperation, we can overcome any
challenge."
</P>
<P>
He expressed the wish that when the organization, which was set
up in 1967, celebrates its 60th anniversary, every child in the
ASEAN region would have a school to go to and be able to read and
write; disease and hunger would become unknown; and the ASEAN
would no longer have any disputes over territories between them.
</P>
<P>
The ASEAN region has been among the fastest growing areas
economically in the world in the past few years.
</P>
<P>
Badawi noted that the current AMM is being held "at a momentous
period in the history of the ASEAN," as both Laos and Myanmar are
now full-fledged members of the grouping.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the belief that "before long Cambodia will take
its rightful place in our association, thus fulfilling the vision
of the ASEAN founding fathers to unite all the Southeast Asian
countries under one regional grouping."
</P>
<P>
Laos and Myanmar officially joined ASEAN Wednesday and their
foreign ministers are participating in the AMM for the first time.
 The accession of Cambodia, which ASEAN had decided to grant
simultaneously with Laos and Myanmar, has been deferred because of
the factional fighting in that country.
</P>
<P>
However, Badawi said uniting all the Southeast Asian countries
under the ASEAN umbrella does not mean a political union.
</P>
<P>
"The ASEAN has been able to survive and progress all these
years because each member state has been free to develop
politically and economically according to its own national ethos,"
he said. "And perhaps the most important principle that has
governed intra-ASEAN relations has been that of non-interference
in one another's internal affairs."
</P>
<P>
He stressed that this principle has stood the test of time and
has contributed to the harmony that prevails today.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
