<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Ends Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, July 24 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar finished
lower today against the US currency.
</P>
<P>
The data released by the Australian Bureau of Statistics showed
wages pressures had ebbed in the May quarter to mark the lowest
year-to-year rise in almost three years.
</P>
<P>
Some market participants think the Reserve Bank of Australia
could cut rates as early as tomorrow morning, when it announces
daily banking system details at 9.30 a.m.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar finished at 73.48 US cents, down from
73.74 at Wednesday's close.
</P>
<P>
"The market believes it is a forgone conclusion that the rate
cut is going to happen, there is nothing standing in the way, it's
just a question of when," said National Australia Bank corporate
manager Derek Price.
</P>
<P>
On the cross-rates, the Australian dollar was at 85.08 from
84.99 against the Japanese yen and at 1.3302 from 1.3415 against
the German mark.  
