<HEADLINE> Australian Stocks Down As NAB Below Expectations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, July 24 (Xinhua) -- A lower than expected third
quarter profit result from National Australia Bank Ltd (NAB) and
another drop in the value of gold stocks led to general falls on
the local share market today.
</P>
<P>
"The market was affected by NAB's third quarter result which
was a little bit below expectations and that led to a fall in
banking stocks," Nevitts' broker Steve Mayne said.
</P>
<P>
NAB posted a third quarter net profit of 1.643 billion
Australian dollars (1.207 billion US dollars), a figure which sent
the company's share price tumbling 45 cents.
</P>
<P>
Other banks also lost ground with Commonwealth Bank down 20
cents, Westpac was down three cents while ANZ added seven
cents.
</P>
<P>
The all ordinaries index finished down 7.0 points at 2,676.4.
</P>
<P>
National turnover totaled 382.50 million shares traded worth
1.01 billion Australian dollars (742 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The all industrials index ended down 3.7 points to 4,302.2,
while the all resources index fell 10.6 points to 1,409.4.
</P>
<P>
"The gold sector still dragged our market down and the
commodities and gold have really kept a hold on our market for a
while now," Reynolds and Co broker Peter Struk said.
</P>
<P>
The gold index tumbled more than 2.5 percent today to 1,259.2,
with gold bullion closing at 321.00 US dollars an ounce down from
323.85 previously.
</P>
<P>
In the resource sector, BHP's share fell ten cents, WMC shares
dipped six and Rio Tinto was up 13 cents.  
</P>
