<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Uganda Ranks Second in Women Fertility in Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, July 24 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan women have the second
highest fertility rate in Africa, reported local daily "The New
Vision" today.
</P>
<P>
The 1997 Progress of Nations Report by the United Nations
Children Fund was quoted as saying that with an average of seven
children per woman, Uganda ranks second to Niger whose rate is
only slightly higher.
</P>
<P>
It said Uganda's per capita income is 240 U.S. Dollars while
Niger 220 Dollars.
</P>
<P>
Mauritius with a per capita income of 3,380 Dollars, Morocco
with 1,110 Dollars and Egypt with 790 Dollars have Africa's
lowest fertility rates, with between two and three children per
woman, according to the report.
</P>
<P>
It said with Ethiopian women as Africa's third most fertile,
Angola, Malawi and Mali are ranked fourth with a rate of six
children per woman.
</P>
<P>
Tanzania and Kenya with five children per woman have 120
Dollars and 280 Dollars per capita income respectively, said the
report which will be launched soon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
