<DOCNO> XIE19970724.0175 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mkapa Wants Ruling Party Manifesto to be Revised </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, July 24 (Xinhua) -- Tanzanian President
Benjamin Mkapa has proposed an immediate review of his ruling
party's 1995 Election Manifesto to short list objectives which
can be achieved before the next general elections.
</P>
<P>
According to local press today, opening the Revolutionary
Party's (CCM) ordinary National Executive Committee (NEC) session
here on Wednesday, Mkapa said he has realized that the manifesto
was overloaded with promises which could not be fulfilled due to
lack of money.
</P>
<P>
"Our new manifesto must remain with development projects which
we are sure beyond doubt we will implement in the remaining three
years before the next elections," he said.
</P>
<P>
Mkapa added, "otherwise, we are free to remain with the
current manifesto and wait to be judged by our voters for
embracing many things but with no tangible results."
</P>
<P>
He said Tanzania is a vast country which needs a lot of
resources for recurrent expenditure and for servicing core social
sectors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
