<HEADLINE> HK's Return Offers Opportunities for Shenzhen: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, July 24 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's return to the
motherland provides unprecedented opportunities for the
development of Shenzhen, the city's mayor Li Zibin told Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
It is well known that Hong Kong is a major financial, trading,
shipping, information and tourism center. After its return, both
the central government and Hong Kong's regional government will be
engaged in retaining Hong Kong's prosperity and stability, the
mayor said.
</P>
<P>
"Being a neighbor of Hong Kong, Shenzhen can benefit from the
radiating force of Hong Kong's new economic expansion," Li said.
</P>
<P>
The two are expected to become complementary in terms of space
for economic expansion, and the cost of products, new technology
and resources, he said.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong enjoys a mature market economy, which to great extent
symbolizes the practice of economic management worldwide. In this
sense, Shenzhen can boldly learn from Hong Kong in its economic
restructuring so as to retain its role as an experimental pioneer
in China, the mayor said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he noted that tremendous achievements across the
country, especially in Shanghai, the Pearl River Delta and the
southern part of Jiangxi Province, have posed great challenges to
Shenzhen.
</P>
<P>
"Facing the opportunities and challenges, we feel that it is
even more urgent to retain Shenzhen's role as a special economic
zone in pushing forward economic restructuring," Li said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
