<HEADLINE> Thai Military Suspends Purchase of Armored Vehicles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, July 24 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's armed forces have
decided to shelve their plans to purchase armored personnel
carriers and tanks in the wake of the country's current economic
recession.
</P>
<P>
The Bangkok Post today quoted Yutthasak Sasiprapa, permanent
secretary for defense, as saying that armed forces Supreme
Commander Gen. Mongkol Ampornpisith had asked the army to postpone
the purchase plan to save foreign reserves.
</P>
<P>
The 520 million baht (17.3 million U.S. dollars) saved will
instead be used in a residential project for armed forces
personnel, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The suspended procurement for armored vehicles will be reviewed
in the next fiscal year beginning October 1, 1997, said Yutthasak.
</P>
