<HEADLINE> First Medical Consultation Network in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 24 (Xinhua) -- China's first medical consultation
network linking Beijing Hospital and the Shenzhen Medi-Care Center
went online on July 22.
</P>
<P>
Experts from the two facilities christened the network by
conducting medical consultations related to the case of an elderly
septuagenarian male who had suffered from abdominal pains for 40
years.
</P>
<P>
Health Minister Chen Minzhang joined Zhou Deqing, vice-minister
of Posts and Telecommunications and Shenzhen Party Committee
Secretary Li Youwei in cutting the ribbon to mark the opening of
the network.
</P>
<P>
The network features state-of-the-art medical and
communications equipment permitting doctors in the two cities to
rapidly exchange audio and visual information.
</P>
<P>
The network also enables doctors to engage in long-term
consultations related to surgical procedures. 
</P>
