<HEADLINE> Pakistan Official to Visit Iran for Talks on Afghan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 24 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Additional Foreign
Secretary Iftikhar Murshid will visit Iran next Monday in a bid to
speed up the on-going shuttle diplomacy to resolve the Afghan
crisis, according to a local press report today.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Tehran, Murshid will discuss with Iranian
leaders the proposals of holding an intra-Afghan dialogue for a
broad-based government in Afghanistan, an official source was
quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Murshid's tour is following a visit to Iran by an Afghan
anti-Taliban alliance leader Abdul Malik who held talks with
Iranian Foreign Minister Ali Akbar Velayati in Tehran recently,
the report said.
</P>
<P>
Before going to Iran, Murshid will visit on Saturday
Mazar-e-Sharif, stronghold of the Afghan anti-Taliban alliance in
the north of the country, said the report.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the report quoted a diplomat as saying that
Murshid's shuttle diplomacy for peace in the Afghanistan is
heading towards nowhere.
</P>
<P>
This is because the warring factions are maintaining a rigid
position on the issue of release of prisoners and demilitarization
of Kabul, according to the diplomat.  
