his hotel last night about one hour after the meeting ended.
</P>
<P>
Ranariddh arrived at Jakarta airport at around 4 p.m.. The
visit was part of his trip to ASEAN (Southeast Asian Nations)
countries to win support after being ousted from his country
following a military conflict with Second Prime Minister Hun Sen.
</P>
<P>
Ranariddh has urged ASEAN to isolate Hun Sen, who rejected a
bid by the grouping to mediate in the Cambodian crisis.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN, which groups Brunei, Indonesia, Malaysia, the
Philippines, Singapore, Thailand and Vietnam, has frozen
Cambodia's membership which should have gone ahead Wednesday at a
special meeting in Kuala Lumpur. 
