Davenport also sailed further while fifth-seeded Mary Pierce of
France and No. 8 Lisa Raymond became the victims of seeds.
</P>
<P>
Coetzer beat Meilen Tu 6-2, 6-0 in a match that took place on
an adjacent court along with Hingis against Maleeva.
</P>
<P>
Davenport defeated Sandra Cacic 6-2,6-2.
</P>
<P>
Pierce lost 3-6, 6-1, 6-4 to Luxembourg's Anne Kremer, who just
finished her first year at Stanford, and Raymond lost 6-4, 6-3 to
Elena Likhovtseva of Russia. 
