<HEADLINE> China Reports New Oil Finds in Northwest Basin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, July 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese petroleum geologists have
discovered a structure that is rich in oil and natural gas
reserves in Kala Yorgun on the northern Tarim Basin of the
Taklimakan Desert.
</P>
<P>
It is quite likely that high-yield oil and gasfields will be
found in the area, say experts, who explain that the geological
structure has different oil-bearing strata.
</P>
<P>
The Tarim Basin has a 560,000-sq.km. area, with the central
part being the Taklimakan Desert. Over the past eight years,
exploration teams from across the country have worked here and
have found 27 large industrial oil-bearing structures.
</P>
<P>
They have discovered ten oil and gasfields with combined oil
and gas reserves of 440 million tons, five of which have begun
producing. The oilfields produced 3.1 million tons of petroleum
last year.
</P>
<P>
A test gas well, Yudong No.2, was sunk in the region by the
Tarim Oil Exploration Headquarters this June and there were good
gas indications down to 5,350 m.
</P>
<P>
Tests done at the well indicated high-yield industrial gas,
proving that the area has plenty of oil and gas reserves.
</P>
<P>
An official at the Tarim Oil Exploration Headquarters told
reporters that Yudong No. 2 is the first high-yield gas well
discovered in the Tarim Basin this year and a 60-sq.km. area
around the test well has conditions favorable for oil exploration.
</P>
<P>
The official says that the headquarters is gathering the best
workers to quickly determine oil reserves in Kala Yorgun and to
conduct further exploration in adjacent areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
