<HEADLINE> Enqvist Rolls past Spadea in Infiniti Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 23 (Xinhua) -- Sweden's Thomas Enqvist cruised
into the quarter-finals of the 303,000 US dollars Infiniti Open by
rolling past American Vincent Spadea 7-6 (7-4), 6-1 on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Enqvist, second-seeded and eighth-ranked, is playing his first
tournament following a 12-week layoff after tearing a couple of
tendons in his left foot. The injury forced the 23-year-old Swede
to miss the summer session, including the French Open and
Wimbledon Championships.
</P>
<P>
But he showed no effects of the injury, easily reaching the
next round's clash against unseeded Dane Kenneth Carlsen, who
ousted Armenian Sargis Sargsian 6-4, 3-6, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
In night action, third seed Mark Philippoussis overcame another
slow start to power past fellow Australian Sandon Stolle 3-6, 6-4,
6-3.
</P>
<P>
In the day's lone upset, unseeded Frenchman Guillaume Raoux
beat fifth-seeded Patrick Rafter 6-4, 7-6 (7-5), dashing any hopes
of an Australian quarter-final clash between Davis Cup teammates.
</P>
</TEXT>
