<HEADLINE> Libertadores Semi-finals Left Finely Balanced </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, July 23 (Xinhua) -- The South American
Liberadores Cup resumes action of semi-finals on Wednesday, seeing
the two home teams managed single-goal victories in first leg
games.
</P>
<P>
Racing Club, winners of the competition in 1967, beat Peru's
Sporting Cristal 3-2 in Buenos Aires while Brazilians Cruzeiro
beat Colo Colo of Chile 1-0 in Belo Horizonte.
</P>
<P>
The semi-finalists had to wait almost two months for the ties
as the tournament was interrupted to make way for June's Copa
America and two rounds of World Cup qualifying matches.
</P>
<P>
In Buenos Aires, Argentina's Racing Club were leading 3-1
through two goals from Claudio Ubeda and one from Diego Martin
Vilallonga until Luis Bonet pulled a crucial goal back for
Sporting five minutes from the end.
</P>
<P>
Cruzeiro's goal came through a blunder of Colo Colo goalkeeper
Marcelo Ramirez, who tried to dribble the ball out of his area but
lost it to Cruzeiro striker Cleisson. 
</P>
</TEXT>
