<HEADLINE> ASEAN to Consider Carefully on Cambodia's Entry: Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PETALING JAYA, MALAYSIA, July 24 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian Prime
Minister Mahathir Mohamad said today that ASEAN would take serious
consideration of any request by Cambodia for its admission into
ASEAN when the group is satisfied with the credibility of the
process taking place there.
</P>
<P>
"We are watching the developments there and as soon as we are
satisfied and they (Cambodia) continue to wish to join ASEAN, we
will take serious consideration of that," he told reporters after
inaugurating the 30th ASEAN Ministerial Meeting here.
</P>
<P>
The Malaysian prime minister did not rule out any possibility
of Cambodia to be a member of ASEAN, adding that "its admission
may be possible this year."
</P>
<P>
On ASEAN's decision to defer Cambodia's entry which was
originally scheduled on July 23 along with Myanmar and Laos,
Mahathir said ASEAN did not accept the legitimacy of the process
in Cambodia in which its First Prime Minister Norodom Narariddh
was moved.
</P>
<P>
Asked for his view on the reaction of Cambodia's Second Prime
Minister Hun Sen Wednesday on the ASEAN decision of not admitting
Cambodia as scheduled, Mahathir said that, it is ASEAN that
decides, not the one who wants to join. To be a member of ASEAN,
certain requirements must be met, he added.
</P>
<P>
On ASEAN's role on the Cambodian issue, he said if Cambodia
considers that ASEAN can do something, "we will see what we can do
for it." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
