<HEADLINE> Criminal Cases Drop in Russia This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 23 (Xinhua) -- The criminal cases put on record
totalled 1.19 million in the first half of this year in Russia, a
9.8 percent decrease over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The Russian Interior Ministry said recently that in the first
six months, there were 694,000 serious criminal cases, 122,000
economic cases and 14,000 murder cases, which were less than those
in the same period last year. But swindling, robbing and bribery
cases increased by 9.3 percent, 2.2 percent and 4.4 percent
respectively.
</P>
<P>
The ministry also said teenagers involved in criminal cases
were 80,000 and 358,000 criminals have no fixed income. 
</P>
