<HEADLINE> Chinese Hybrid Rice Developer Given New Honor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, July 24 (Xinhua) -- Yuan Longping, a noted agronomist
in central China's Hunan Province, will be awarded the title of
"Pioneer Scientist".
</P>
<P>
The title will be conferred at an international symposium on
crop genetics in Mexico from August 17 to 22. Yuan recently
received a letter from Shivaji Pandey, chairman of the preparatory
committee, recommending him for the title.
</P>
<P>
More than 400 geneticists, biologists, molecular biologists,
and agronomists from all over the world are being invited to the
meeting.
</P>
<P>
Yuan has devoted his life to the research on high-yield hybrid
rice, something that has won him fame as the "father of hybrid
rice" and several international scientific awards.
</P>
<P>
Hybrid rice developed by Yuan is being grown in more than 20
countries. It generally gives a 20-percent greater yield than
local crops. 
</P>
