<HEADLINE> Northeast China Port Attracting More Overseas Businessmen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, July 24 (Xinhua) -- Dalian, a port city in northeast
China's Liaoning Province, where foreign companies have opened
1,449 representative offices, has become one of the five Chinese
cities with the most overseas businessmen, according to an
official in charge of foreign trade and economic co-operation.
</P>
<P>
The city has a strong export team consisting of foreign trade
companies, manufacturers with an export license, rural and
township enterprises, and overseas-backed enterprises.
</P>
<P>
There are 104 foreign trade companies, large and medium-sized
enterprises, and scientific research institutes in the city with
an import and export license.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition business has also become a new part of this
city's foreign trade, and more than 50 exhibitions and fairs of
various kinds have been held since last July, when the city's
International Exhibition Center was completed.
</P>
<P>
The city now has 6,000 overseas-backed businesses with 4.17
billion U.S. dollars worth of investment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
