<HEADLINE> Report on Proposed Uruguay-Argentina Bridge Due Soon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, July 23 (Xinhua) -- Uruguayan Foreign Minister
Alvaro Ramos left for the United States today to receive a
preliminary report from Harvard University on the feasibility of
a proposed bridge connecting Uruguay with Argentina.
</P>
<P>
The bridge, spanning the Rio de la Plata estuary and the
longest in the world once completed, will link the port city of
Colonia in southern Uruguay with the Argentinan capital Buenos
Aires.
</P>
<P>
The Harvard Institute for International Development was asked
to do a follow-up investigation and evaluation of the viability of
the project, including traffic flows, load capability,
construction cost, financial and economic projections and
environmental impact.
</P>
<P>
Ramos said recently the bridge "will be a huge integration and
socio-economic project, considering the development model that has
been followed in the country for the past 20 years." 
</P>
