<DOCNO> XIE19970724.0258 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin: Do a Good Job of Family Planning (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 24 (Xinhua) -- General Secretary of the Central
Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC) and Chinese
President Jiang Zemin said the over-population warning must be
sounded constantly, and continued efforts must be made to
guarantee that China controls its population within 1.3 billion by
the end of this century.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the remark at a national forum on family planning
and environmental protection held on March 8. Xinhua issued the
full text of Jiang's speech made at the forum.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said China's achievements in family planning have
attracted worldwide attention. China controlled its population
growth properly and in accordance with its plan last year, which
marked a good beginning for family planning during the Ninth
Five-Year Plan period (1996-2000).
</P>
<P>
He stressed that, however, we must kept sober-minded as China
has a large population and annually newly-born babies number some
21 million. The net increase of population in China is 13 million
each year.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that family planning work is weak in some areas, and
some provinces and autonomous regions are experiencing "baby
booms."
</P>
<P>
He added that family planning work is arduous and must not be
slackened at any time. He added that we must not be unrealistically
optimistic just because the country has fulfilled its population
growth targets in the past few years.
</P>
<P>
He also urged the areas with big population problems to enhance
their confidence in family planning and not to become dispirited.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970724.0259 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin: Do a Good Job of Family Planning (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jiang said China has found a way to solve the population
problem with Chinese characteristics in reining in the fast
population growth, and created much valuable experience.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Zemin stressed that we must insist on following the
practices and experiences which have proved to be correct, and
continue to perfect them.
</P>
<P>
He said, family planning must be listed as one of the important
parts of promoting socialist ethical and cultural progress.
</P>
<P>
Jiang also called on officials in charge of family planning to
improve their work style and professional ethics.
</P>
<P>
He said China must focus its family planning work on the rural
areas, as the population control in rural areas, especially the
poor areas, is a big problem.
</P>
<P>
He said one of the major reasons for the underdevelopment of
the poverty-stricken areas is that the population growth in those
areas is too fast.
</P>
<P>
Jiang pointed out that aid-the-poor work must be combined with
family planning.
</P>
<P>
He said poor families, villages, townships and counties doing a
good job of family planning should enjoy preferential policies in
receiving aid-the-poor funds, household resettlement in better
areas, technology training and labor export.
</P>
<P>
After they shake off poverty they can lead other poor families,
villages, townships or counties to meet their needs for food and
clothing, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
