<HEADLINE> Chileans Invest 4.30 Billion Dollars Overseas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, July 23 (Xinhua) -- Chileans have invested a total of
4.30 billion U.S. dollars overseas, including 548 million dollars
in the first half of this year, Chile's central bank said today.
</P>
<P>
As most of the Chilean investments went to South America,
Argentina was the biggest recipient with 1.86 billion dollars,
followed by Peru with 340 million and Bolivia with 267 million.
</P>
<P>
Other major markets for Chilean investors were Central America
and the Caribbean, which together received a total of 796 million
dollars, including 379 million in the first six months of the year.
</P>
<P>
The official figures are conservative compared with those from
the private Santiago Chamber of Commerce, which put the overseas
investment total at 16 billion dollars involving more than 250
companies and 600 projects. 
</P>
