<HEADLINE> Bayern Beat Dortmund to Reach League Cup Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, July 23 (Xinhua) -- Bayern Munich warmed up for the new
season with an impressive 2-0 victory over European Cup winners
Borussia Dortmund on Wednesday to reach the final of the inaugural
German League Cup.
</P>
<P>
Goals from new Brazilian signing Giovane Elber and
international defender Markus Babbel helped the Bundesliga
champions move towards a clash with VfB Stuttgart in Saturday's
final in Leverkusen.
</P>
<P>
Stuttgart beat Karlsruhe 3-0 on Tuesday in the other semifinal
of the lucrative competition which brings together the top six
teams of last year's league championship as the curtain raiser to
the season which starts next month.
</P>
<P>
Elber put Bayern in front with a shot from just outside the
penalty area after 29 minutes and a header by Babbel from a cross
by new French signing Bixente Lizarazu allowed the Munich club to
seal the win. 
</P>
