<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> "Family Planning and Environmental Protection Work Urgent" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin has
attached great importance to the two basic state policies of
family planning and environmental protection, saying that they are
both closely related to China's overall social and economic
development.
</P>
<P>
He made the remark March 8 at a national forum on family
planning and environmental protection. Xinhua today issued the
full text of his speech at the forum.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that the two causes are closely interconnected with
each other -- if one fails to succeed then the other will also be
greatly hampered.
</P>
<P>
With a large population and limited per capita natural
resources, China is facing great difficulties in maintaining and
improving its ecological environment, Jiang noted.
</P>
<P>
He said that the nation's socialist construction should
unswervingly concentrate on economic development to boost the
national economy, and at the same time take full consideration of
population control and environmental protection work so as to
ensure sustained development.
</P>
<P>
The education and publicity work on these two state policies
needs to be further enhanced, the president said, and they should
be regarded as important parts of the nation's material and
ideological progress. 
</P>
</TEXT>
