<HEADLINE> Wojcik to Coach Polish Soccer Team </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, July 23 (Xinhua) -- Former Olympic coach Janusz Wojcik
has been picked up to become the new Polish national team coach,
the Polish Soccer Association (PZPN) said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Wojcik, 44, replaces Antoni Piechniczek who quit last month
after a 2-0 home defeat to England which ended Poland's hopes of
qualifying for the 1998 World Cup.
</P>
<P>
In 1992, Wojcik guided Poland to a silver medal at the
Barcelona Olympics. He had spent the last three years coaching in
the United Arab Emirates.
</P>
<P>
"Simply, the national side will consist of Poland's best
players," Wojcik was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
In 1993 Wojcik guided Legia Warsaw to the national club
championship but the title was later taken away from them because
of alleged game-rigging. 
