<HEADLINE> Bulls Announce Re-signing of Coach Jackson </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 23 (Xinhua) -- The reigning NBA champion
Chicago Bulls announced in Chicago on Wednesday that head coach
Phil Jackson re-signed with the team for the 1997-98 season.
</P>
<P>
Team chairman Jerry Reinsdorf said in a statement that the
one-year pact made Jackson the highest-paid "pure" coach in the
league, which excluded coaches who also act as their teams'
general managers.
</P>
<P>
Terms of the agreement were not disclosed.
</P>
<P>
Jackson, the only coach superstar Michael Jordan said he would
play for, has a career record of 96-35 in the postseason and
his .733 winning percentage is the best in NBA playoff history.
</P>
<P>
Last season, Jackson became the third coach in league history
to win five championships. 
</P>
