<HEADLINE> Serb Team Beats Croatia Zagreb 1-0 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, July 23 (Xinhua) -- Partizan Belgrade beat Croatia
Zagreb 1-0 in the first official soccer match between Serbian and
Croatian clubs since the war in Yugoslavia broke out in 1991.
</P>
<P>
There were tough security measures around the stadium during
the game as the police body-searched all fans as they
entered. Riot police were deployed around the pitch but there were
no major incidents.
</P>
<P>
The only goal for Partizan was scored in the 84th minute by
forward Dragan Isailovic from close range after a neat combination
within the penalty area.
</P>
<P>
The two countries' European Champions Cup qualification clash,
which media in both nations billed as historic and do-or-die,
returns to Croatian capital Zagreb for the second leg match in a
week's time. 
</P>
