<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EC Decides on Controls on Movement of Meat, Bone Meal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, July 23 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission today
decided to impose controls on the movement of meat and bone meal
between the European Union (EU) member states.
</P>
<P>
On a proposal from Franz Fischler, EU commissioner for
agriculture and rural development, detailed rules are being
planned to be laid down for the movement of meat and bone meal
which has not been produced to the new standards to other member
states for incineration or use as fuel.
</P>
<P>
The proposal includes prior authorization of the member states
of destination, labeling of the material to the effect that it
cannot be used for feeding and transport in a sealed container
directly to the incinerator.
</P>
<P>
The commission has conducted inspections and meetings with its
member states, which have shown that the required standards are
not being fully applied across the EU.
</P>
<P>
It notes that some member states are not applying the standards
to mammalian waste from animals fit for human consumption while
others need more time to upgrade their plants. 
</P>
</TEXT>
