<HEADLINE> Albright to Pressure Hun Sen to Accept ASEAN Mediation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 23 (Xinhua) -- U.S. Secretary of State
Madeleine Albright said today the United States will do what it
can to pressure Cambodian co-Prime Minister Hun Sen into accepting
mediation in the recent Cambodia crisis and restore the coalition
government there.
</P>
<P>
She made the remarks at the Los Angeles World Affairs Council
before flying to Kuala Lumpur where she will attend the annual
meeting of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN).
</P>
<P>
Albright said Hun Sen through his spokesman appeared to have
accepted ASEAN's offer of mediation and promised to restore the
previous coalition government and observe the rule of law.
</P>
<P>
"The United States will use its leverage and do all we can in
partnership with others to see that Hun Sen's words are translated
into concrete action," Albright said.
</P>
<P>
"This will be one of our primary goals at the (ASEAN) meetings
this weekend in Kuala Lumpur," she added.
</P>
<P>
In her speech, Albright expressed U.S. unhappiness over ASEAN
members agreeing to admit Myanmar (Burma) as its new member this
year.
</P>
<P>
The United States imposed a ban in April on new U.S. investment
in Myanmar and asked ASEAN not to accept Myanmar into the regional
organization, which, however, was rejected by ASEAN. 
</P>
