<HEADLINE> EC Decided to Renew Committees on Consumer Health </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, July 23 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission today
decided to renew eight scientific committees in the field of
consumer health and food safety.
</P>
<P>
The European Union (EU)'s executive agency aims at
strengthening the coherence of the existing scientific committees
and at redefining the activities of some of them, according to a
press release issued here today.
</P>
<P>
The commission noted that the three principles which must be at
the basis of the good performance of the scientific committees
were the excellence of their members, their independence and the
transparency of their advice.
</P>
<P>
It said that this decision was "a significant step" towards the
implementation of its new approach announced in a communication on
consumer health and food safety which has been recently adopted.
</P>
<P>
The scientific committees which have been established are on
food, animal nutrition, animal health and welfare, veterinary
public health, plants, cosmetic products and non-food products
intended for consumers, medicaments and medical materials, and
toxicity, ecotoxicity and the environment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
