<HEADLINE> Information Society Needs to Be Enhanced Socially: EU </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, July 23 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission said
today that the European Union (EU) needed to further strengthen
the social dimension of the information society to take advantage
of the accompanying opportunities.
</P>
<P>
In a press release issued here today, the EU's executive body
argued the EU should "take full advantage" of the opportunities
offered by new information and communication technologies in terms
of job creation, prosperity and quality of life.
</P>
<P>
In a communication adopted today, the commission set out a
strategy for achieving this objective at national, European and
international levels.
</P>
<P>
Presented by Padraig Flynn, EU commissioner for employment and
social affairs, and Martin Bangemann, commissioner for industrial
affairs, the communication summarized the challenges which lie
ahead in reconciling social, economic and technological goals.
</P>
<P>
In particular, it identified a set of nearly 60 actions to
develop the social dimension of the information society in EU
initiatives, policies and programs at regional, national and
international levels.
</P>
<P>
Sources said that the communication formed part of the
commission's Rolling Action Plan -- Europe at the Forefront of the
Global Information Society. 
