<HEADLINE> Jordan, U.S. Discuss Defense Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, July 23 (Xinhua) -- King Hussein of Jordan today met
visiting Commander-in-Chief of the United States Central Command
Lieutenant General Binford Peay and discussed bilateral defense
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Peay arrived here earlier in the day on a 2-day official
visit, Radio Jordan reported.
</P>
<P>
Washington highly values the king's efforts towards peace in
the Middle East and his policies about security and stability in
the region, Peay said.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was also attended by Chairman of the Jordanian
Joint Chiefs of Staff Field Marshal Abdul Hafez Marei Kaabneh.
</P>
<P>
