military exercises for this year, in March and May respectively.
</P>
<P>
Last December, Jordan received 100 million U.S. dollars
military aid from the U.S., as part of a total of 300 million
dollars assistance pledged by the current U.S. administration.
</P>
<P>
The remaining 200 million dollars of the assistance will be
spent on 16 F-16 jet fighters which the U.S. is expected to
deliver by the end of 1997.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. also gave Jordan the none-NATO alliance status, which
guaranteed better access for the kingdom for U.S. military
equipment. 
